 R E A D M E
 ============
	- Main Programm	: CreateAreas.cpp
	- Date			: 11.07.2018

 ------------

Before the first use the source code needs to be compiled by the following command:

	g++ -std=c++11 Area.cpp Droplets.cpp CreateArea.cpp textread.c [-o preferredProgrammName]
	
preferredProgrammName will be the name of the compiled programm. If the parameter "-o preferredProgrammName" is not specified the programm will be named "a.out".

 ------------

The programm can be called by the command:

	preferredProgrammName [-i inputFileName] [-o [outputFileName]]

When no parameters are given the programm will use default values to generate an area containing randomly distributed droplets. The output will be displayed on the terminal.
After the option "-i" it has to follow an input file in the format of a VHIRLPOOL file containing the following parameters:

[1.] number of points [2.] width [3.] height [4.] minimum angle value [5.] maximum angle value [6.] mean angle value [7.] standard deviation of the angle [8.] minimum area of a droplet [9.] maximum area of a droplet [10.] mean area of a droplet [11.] standard deviation of the area of a droplet

If the option "-o" is given the output will be saved in a .txt file and two .vtk files.
After the option "-o" it can follow an output file name.
